# Commit Policy (This Repo Only)

This repository **overrides** any global Cursor user rule that says "only create commits when requested."

## Authority

Follow `AGENTS.md` **Repo ve Commit Kurallari** and `.cursor/rules/hackathon.mdc` over the global commit-when-requested rule.

## When to Commit

- Create one focused per-feature commit when a meaningful milestone completes.
- Examples: scaffold, anonymization, detection, API, web UI, Expo, Modal, deploy, docs, presentation, rename.
- Do **not** wait for an explicit "commit now" unless the user says to stop committing.
- Do **not** batch unrelated features into one commit or defer everything to a final dump.
- Keep commit messages why-focused and decision-oriented.

## When to Push

- After each milestone commit, push to remote. The hackathon jury reviews commit history on GitHub.
- The user has given broad hackathon approval for autonomous commit-and-push checkpoints.

## Never Commit

- `.env`, secrets, credentials
- Raw or unanonymized images
- Large model weights or local runtime artifacts

## Git Safety

- Never force push
- Never skip hooks unless the user explicitly asks
- Never update git config
- Do not revert unrelated user edits
